    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="upa.00076.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><hi rend="underline">Kirkwood</hi> (Glendale) America<ptr
                            target="upa.00076_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1883-04-15" rend="right">April 15 '83</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>I am down here for a few days&#8212;Mrs. <choice>
                    <abbr>S.</abbr>
                    <expan>Stafford</expan>
                </choice> has had a severe fit of illness&#8212;three weeks&#8212;one <hi
                    rend="underline">week quite alarming</hi>&#8212;but is now better&#8212;to day&#8212;is
                up&#8212;&#38; has been down stairs once or twice for a few minutes&#8212;with luck
                &#38; good weather the doctor thinks she will get around again as usual before
                long</p>
            <p>&#8212;Nothing specially new with me&#8212;I keep about as usual&#8212;have had a fair
                winter&#8212;Dr Bucke's book is being printed &#38; is to have your intaglio for a
                    frontispiece<ptr target="upa.00076_n2"/>&#8212;it arouses the strongest opinions
                pro and con&#8212;(Dr B. &#38; several,&#8212;including myself,&#8212;decidedly like
                it)</p>
            <p>Love to you, to your dear <choice>
                    <abbr>M.</abbr>
                    <expan>Mother</expan>
                </choice> &#38; to <choice>
                    <abbr>G</abbr><expan>Grace</expan></choice>.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">W W</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="upa.00076.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
